Utterances: hi, my name is suveksha and i am going to be your nurse today.
Hi.
can you tell me your name and date of birth?
Regina Walker, I was born January 1st . . . [Ms. Walker reports correct birth year.]
do you know where you are?
I'm in the hospital.
can you tell me why you are here?
I was having trouble with the pain from my cancer... I just couldn't take it anymore at home.
can you rate your pain form 0 to 10? (Clarified to Can you rate your current pain level on a scale of 0 to 10?.)
Right now, I'm about a 4 of 10. (Clarified to how I would rate my pain on a scale.)
when did you first notice your pain?
I've been in some pain for a long time, but it reached an unbearable level two days ago.
have you been taking any pain medication?
I believe they are morphine pills. I have one type that is fast acting and another that is effective over a longer period.
sometimes trying non pharmacological techniques can help reduce pain.
Thanks. Perhaps that could help me.
where do you feel your pain?
Well, everywhere really . . . These past days I've felt it mostly in my ribs and legs but even my bones hurt.
how would you describe your pain?
I can feel it all over my body . . . It's a sharp pain in my bones, my legs, and my ribs. It's been getting much worse over the past two days.
what cause your pain worse?
It's my cancer... I'm aware how bad it's gotten.
what is the aggravating factors of pain?
Nothing makes the pain worse, nothing makes it better. It's just constant and relentless.
are you allergic to medication?
I'm allergic to penicillin, but that's it.
are you allergic to any food?
No. Not that I know of currently.
when did you last took your home medication?
I took some of the fast-acting morphine this morning, but it wasn't much help. Pain just cut right through it. I haven't yet had my Hyzaar.
when did you took long-acting morphine? (No matching questions found.)
when was the last time you took long-acting morphine?
At home? I take the long acting morphine every 12 hours, so my last dose was last night. I tried to use the fast acting this morning, but the pain was just too much.
do you take any illicit drugs?
No, I do not.
how many glass of water do you drink in a day?
Not very much. Probably a glass here and there I suppose.
how often do you urinate ?
I haven't been going any more or less than usual if that's what you mean.
what was your most recent meal?
Let's see, I had a few bites of yogurt last night before bed... I think that was the last time I had anything.
do you have any preference for your hospice care?

I want to allow things to take their course . . . it's time for me to stop fighting and just enjoy the time I have left in what little ways I can. My husband and I have chosen an assisted living residence near my home where I'll go for hospice care. I have been told that they can help me with the pain there .  . . and it's close enough that my husband can be with me.
who is your advance directives? (Clarified to Do you have an advance directive?.)
Yes, all my affairs should be in order. (Clarified to if I have an advance directive.)
do you have head and neck pain? (Clarified to Do you have any problems with your head?.)
My head feels just fine, that's not where I'm having the pain. (Clarified to if I have head problems.)
it is important to assess your body system for better care.
You're kind for filling me in.
do you have trouble breathing?
No, I don't have any breathing difficulties.
do you have any cardiovascular issue?
No, I've never had heart trouble.
how often do you have bowel movement?
Well, I've been constipated for about four days now, I can't seem to make anything happen there.
do you have any neurological issue?
Yes, I've been feeling quite weak lately.
you must be feeling weak because of your cancer.
Thank you. Your kindness is felt.
do you have any psychological problem?
No, not specifically . . . I have been feeling somewhat anxious lately though.
do you have depression?
I have my ups and downs. Nothing so down I'd call depression, though.
who do you live with?
My husband and I live in at home together, and our son visits just about every day.
do you feel safe at home?
Of course, I've never felt threatened at home.
can you bath alone?
I don't bathe on my own anymore. My husband helps me, especially with getting in and out of the shower, and we have a shower bench that I sit on.
do you need help dressing?
I don't have any trouble dressing myself.
do you need assistance to get to go to toilet?
Yes, when I have to go it's a bit of an ordeal to get up and down.
do you usually need help transferring? (Clarified to Are you using assistance when transferring?.)

Well, I have the most trouble getting up from any sort of lying position, so I spend most of my time in bed. My husband usually gives me a hand when I need to get up. (Clarified to if I am getting assistance when transferring.)
have you experienced any urinary incontinence? (Clarified to Do you have trouble controlling urination?.)
I'm still in control of my bladder and bowels, thankfully. (Clarified to if I have trouble controlling when I urinate.)
do you need hep with feeding? (No matching questions found.)
are you able to cook for yourself?
Well I used to cook more, but I just don't have the strength for it anymore.
do you have trouble sleeping?
Yes, my sleep has been rather poor lately due to the pain.
do you feel confused?
No, not currently.
do you have recent falls? (Clarified to Have you fallen recently?.)
No, I haven't had any recent falls. (Clarified to if I have fallen recently.)
do you have recent skin breakdown? (No matching questions found.)
have you notice any recent skin breakdown? (Clarified to Has your skin changed?.)
I wouldn't call it much of a problem but my skin has been feeling thinner than normal. (Clarified to if my skin has changed.)
aging can also cause thinner skin.
Thank you for saying that. Really.
do you have recent change in weight? (Clarified to Has your weight changed recently?.)
Yes, I've lost a bit of weight in the past two months or so. (Clarified to if I have had weight changes recently.)
do you have any dental problems?
No, I don't have any problems with my mouth, jaw, or teeth.
has your appetite changed recently?
My appetite has been rather small lately, I haven't been eating too much for the last months.
how has your health affected your social activity? (Clarified to How does your health affect your life?.)

Well, the pain cancer gives me is unbearable. I can't go to church, I can't drive, I can barely get out of bed. . . I'm not sure what else there is to say about it. (Clarified to how my health affects my life.)
what do you feel about your health? (Clarified to How do you perceive your health?.)
I'd say my health is poor in general. I'm quite aware of the situation I'm in. (Clarified to how I perceive my health.)
I know having cancer makes you feel you have poor health.
I appreciate the sympathy.
are you tried? (No matching questions found.)
are you tired?
I've been feeling tired all of the time lately.
when was your recent hospitalization?
Well, I haven't been hospitalized for the past three months, but I had some cancer treatments I underwent around three months ago.
what health condition did your parents has?
My father had pretty high cholesterol and blood pressure--he liked his steak, you know. He had type 2 diabetes as well.
what health condition did your mother has? (Clarified to Does your mother have health problems?.)
My mother was hypertensive and had high cholesterol, but she passed away from a stroke some time ago. (Clarified to if my mother has health problems.)
have you had any surgical history? (Clarified to Have you had any other surgeries?.)
I had some surgeries done, the mastectomy for my cancer about four years ago and a hernia repair some twenty years back. (Clarified to if I have had any other surgeries.)
do you have any other health condition?
Yes, I have stage IV breast cancer and hypertension.
do you feel you have being abused financially?

No, no one in my family would ever steal from me . . . they would never do that. My husband is the one responsible for my . . . for my will, and our finances. I trust him unconditionally to take care of those matters.
that is so good that you have a family to take care when you are sick.
I appreciate the good will.
it is important to assess abuse in each patient.
I see. Thats helpful to know.
how is your pain now?
It's better now than before, but I can still feel it there.
do you want to try other techniques to help your pain.
Thanks much for that.
sometimes applying heat and cold to the affected area can help reduce pain.
I appreciate the information.
meditating has helped patient to reduce pain by reducing focus from the pain. (No matching questions found.)
do you have any concerns?
Yes, thanks very much.
do you need anything?
Not right now, I'm just fine.
if you need anything just call me i am here for you.
I appreciate the good will.
if you want to talk about anything i will be available for you.
I appreciate the sympathy.
